With spring on the way, most Aussies are getting a haircut.

But a shearing has been especially welcome for Shaun - the sheep who was found wandering the island state of Tasmania with one of the world's heaviest ever fleeces.

The gigantic sheep has now shed 23.5kg of wool, enough to make 40 jumpers and just shy of the world record set by another lost sheep ten years ago.

